1
00:00:02,002 --> 00:00:03,295
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:28,547
FRIEND

3
00:01:34,845 --> 00:01:35,929
I understand.

4
00:01:36,179 --> 00:01:39,600
I can't be your boyfriend,
but I can act like it.

5
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:41,602
Thank you so much.

6
00:01:41,852 --> 00:01:45,063
I'll try my hardest to make you love me.
I promise.

7
00:01:46,857 --> 00:01:50,360
[Light] I'll arrange for her to meet L.
She'll tell me his name

8
00:01:50,527 --> 00:01:53,196
and then I eliminate
the entire Task Force.

9
00:01:53,405 --> 00:01:56,116
And when that's done,
I'll kill her, too.

10
00:01:56,408 --> 00:01:57,326
After all,

11
00:01:57,451 --> 00:02:00,537
she's the only person
who knows Kira's true identity.

12
00:02:00,662 --> 00:02:04,458
The only one.
I can't let her live much longer.

13
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:09,046
So, you'll just pretend?
All right. I guess it's a good start.

14
00:02:09,171 --> 00:02:12,257
Well, now that we've talked about that,
could you show me your Shinigami?

15
00:02:12,341 --> 00:02:13,675
I really wanna see him.

16
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:16,637
[Light] I need her to trust me,
I guess I have to.

17
00:02:16,887 --> 00:02:18,055
Yeah, sure.

18
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:19,723
Could you please turn around?

19
00:02:19,931 --> 00:02:20,849
All right.

20
00:02:28,315 --> 00:02:29,566
You can turn back now.

21
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:30,901
Okay.

22
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,112
Hey there. How's it going?

23
00:02:34,529 --> 00:02:35,822
Oh, look at that.

24
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:38,992
You're a completely different type
of Shinigami than Rem, aren't you?

25
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:41,119
I already know your name.
It's Ryuk, right?

26
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:42,412
Nice to meet you.

27
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,414
Yeah, same here.

28
00:02:44,748 --> 00:02:46,500
Oh, and by the way, Light darling,

29
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,710
do you know how to kill a Shinigami?

30
00:02:49,044 --> 00:02:51,129
[Light] Did you just call me "darling"?

31
00:02:51,505 --> 00:02:54,299
Fine. Then, do you mind
if I call you "Knight" instead?

32
00:02:54,508 --> 00:02:56,927
Because you're like my knight
in shining armor, you know.

33
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:58,804
[sighs] Let's just stick with Light.

34
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:02,808
[Aizawa] So, were you actually
planning to check all of the footage

35
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:05,185
we got from Aoyama on the 22nd
by yourself?

36
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:07,187
That's right. I think it's very likely

37
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:11,066
that Kira and the Second Kira made contact
with each other there on that day.

38
00:03:11,233 --> 00:03:13,443
So, I want to check
all of these tapes personally.

39
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:16,113
-Also, Mr. Yagami?
-Uh, yes?

40
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:18,865
Please ask Mr. Mogi
to start following Light

41
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:20,492
so we can keep tabs on what he's doing.

42
00:03:20,826 --> 00:03:22,285
[Yagami] You want him followed?

43
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:25,288
It's only a slim chance,
but if Light is Kira,

44
00:03:25,414 --> 00:03:26,623
then, there's still a possibility

45
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:30,043
that the second Kira might try
to contact him somehow.

46
00:03:30,502 --> 00:03:32,129
-Very well.
-[door opens]

47
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:34,589
I'm starting to wonder
if Ryuzaki is even human.

48
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:35,757
The guy never sleeps.

49
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:39,261
I saw him sleeping in that
exact same position the other day.

50
00:03:39,428 --> 00:03:41,888
-Huh.
-[Matsuda] No, I'm serious.

51
00:03:42,723 --> 00:03:43,932
Hmm.

52
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:48,270
So, if a Shinigami has feelings
for a human,

53
00:03:48,395 --> 00:03:51,189
and kills someone else
in order to extend that human's life

54
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:53,692
beyond its natural end,
the Shinigami will die?

55
00:03:53,984 --> 00:03:55,193
That's right.

56
00:03:56,027 --> 00:03:57,070
[Ryuk chuckles]

57
00:03:57,320 --> 00:04:00,449
Good luck trying to find a Shinigami
who'd volunteer to do that.

58
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:02,159
That's true.

59
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:04,578
I can't see you ever doing that.

60
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:08,039
By the way, where did you send
all those tapes from?

61
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:10,125
The ones that went to the TV stations?

62
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:13,712
Let's see. Osaka, the first time.
Then Tokyo.

63
00:04:13,837 --> 00:04:15,338
This other one from Nagano.

64
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:17,048
I took the bullet train every time,

65
00:04:17,174 --> 00:04:19,760
so that way the police couldn't pinpoint
my location.

66
00:04:20,135 --> 00:04:22,262
All right, one more thing.
Do you still have

67
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:25,015
the video tapes and envelopes
with your friend's fingerprints on them?

68
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:25,974
Uh-huh.

69
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:29,436
Well, you'll have to dispose of everything
that was used to create those video tapes,

70
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,479
understand?

71
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:34,191
But before you do,
I need you to send one last video.

72
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:36,526
And make sure it's from a place
you haven't used yet.

73
00:04:36,651 --> 00:04:37,778
It should say...

74
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:41,364
"I've decided to stop searching for Kira.

75
00:04:41,865 --> 00:04:43,950
and I'd like to thank
the police department

76
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:45,243
for all of its advice.

77
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:49,206
However, I still plan to help Kira
in his mission.

78
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:53,168
And I hope that in time,
he'll come to see me as an ally.

79
00:04:53,585 --> 00:04:57,297
I will start by punishing criminals
that Kira has yet to judge.

80
00:04:57,672 --> 00:04:58,757
Also...

81
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,761
I will share my power with others
who I feel are worthy

82
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:05,055
and I will encourage them to do the same.

83
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,224
Together, we'll make this world
a better place."

84
00:05:07,516 --> 00:05:08,892
"Share my power"?

85
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:11,978
We'll just add that part
to throw off their investigation.

86
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:14,815
They suspect that there are already
two people with this power,

87
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:17,317
so it wouldn't be a stretch to assume
there could be others.

88
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:20,111
And if they believe the numbers are
growing, then they'll start to panic.

89
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,446
Can you do this?

90
00:05:21,613 --> 00:05:24,574
No need to ask.
Just tell me what to do and I'll do it.

91
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:27,452
I don't care what it is
because I'd do anything for you.

92
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:29,704
[Light] There's one more thing
which is very important.

93
00:05:29,788 --> 00:05:30,831
What's that?

94
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:32,958
If you get arrested by the police,

95
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:35,377
or if you're ever brought in
for questioning,

96
00:05:35,544 --> 00:05:38,588
you can never mention anything
about us or the Death Note.

97
00:05:38,964 --> 00:05:41,007
As long as they don't get a hold
of that notebook,

98
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,926
there's no proof that you did anything.

99
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:45,262
Can you promise to say nothing?

100
00:05:45,679 --> 00:05:46,763
I promise!

101
00:05:47,264 --> 00:05:50,308
So this must mean that we're officially
boyfriend and girlfriend now, aren't we?

102
00:05:50,892 --> 00:05:52,394
Well, sure. I guess.

103
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:54,646
Then, I'd like to add one condition.

104
00:05:54,813 --> 00:05:57,399
You have to go on a date with me
at least once a week.

105
00:05:57,774 --> 00:06:00,902
[sighs]
Unbelievable. She still doesn't get it.

106
00:06:01,278 --> 00:06:03,697
-We can't.
-[gasps] But why?

107
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:06,449
Ugh, it looks like I'm gonna have
to spell this out for you.

108
00:06:06,575 --> 00:06:09,870
L already suspects that I'm Kira,
do you see what I'm saying here?

109
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:13,957
No way! L is amazing.
I mean...

110
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:17,085
Everyone's been saying that he's getting
nowhere with the investigation

111
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:20,672
and that he's a complete idiot and stuff.
But he already knows that much?

112
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:23,258
Anyway, it's all worked out well for me

113
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:26,136
because thanks to that,
I've also been able to get close to L.

114
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:29,389
Huh? You and L are
in contact with each other?

115
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:34,102
Then, that's even more amazing.
This is getting so exciting.

116
00:06:34,436 --> 00:06:36,187
Even though he suspects I'm Kira,

117
00:06:36,271 --> 00:06:39,190
L figures he's safe as long as
I don't know his real name.

118
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:42,360
He came right out and told me who he was,
just to get to me.

119
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:47,324
However, he's only focusing on me
because he has no other suspects.

120
00:06:47,616 --> 00:06:49,534
And he has no evidence.

121
00:06:50,994 --> 00:06:53,705
At this moment,
I'm working with him on the case.

122
00:06:53,872 --> 00:06:56,333
And little by little,
I'm winning his trust.

123
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:59,377
Great. So all you have to do
is take me to where L is,

124
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:01,379
and I can see his real name for you.

125
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:03,673
-[Light] I'm afraid it's not that simple.
-Hm?

126
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:07,052
Listen, it was difficult enough for me
to get close to him.

127
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:11,097
Besides, if all of a sudden,
someone I just met gets too close,

128
00:07:11,181 --> 00:07:13,391
and at the same time,
the police detect changes

129
00:07:13,475 --> 00:07:15,518
in Kira or the Second Kira's behavior,

130
00:07:15,936 --> 00:07:18,688
that person will be suspected
of being the Second Kira.

131
00:07:18,772 --> 00:07:22,067
And, of course, that will put me
under even greater suspicion.

132
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,444
We can't allow them to make
that connection.

133
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:27,322
Which means we can't appear
to be too close to each other.

134
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:29,658
Do you understand what I'm saying?

135
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,494
Well, I think I understand.

136
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:34,704
So, is that why we can't go on dates?

137
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:37,582
We can't be seen in public
because it will look too suspicious?

138
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:38,750
Look...

139
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:41,920
We need to take the time now
to come up with a good plan.

140
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:44,839
Some way that you can see L
without letting him know you exist.

141
00:07:45,006 --> 00:07:45,882
Yeah.

142
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:48,218
[Light] I can't eliminate L without you.

143
00:07:48,385 --> 00:07:51,888
So I'll call you and see you
as often as this situation allows.

144
00:07:52,097 --> 00:07:53,181
You will?

145
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:54,599
-[Light] But...
-[Misa] Oh.

146
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:57,143
... to make sure that our meetings
don't stand out,

147
00:07:57,310 --> 00:08:00,063
I have to make sure that I'm seen
with other girls, okay?

148
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:01,856
Huh? What do you mean?

149
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:03,942
You're seriously going to date
other girls?

150
00:08:04,526 --> 00:08:05,777
Yeah, more or less.

151
00:08:05,944 --> 00:08:07,862
-[yelling] I don't want you to.
-Huh?

152
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:12,534
If I see you with another girl,
I'll kill her.

153
00:08:13,410 --> 00:08:14,577
Scary!

154
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:16,454
Look, sweetie...

155
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:18,123
"Sweetie"? [laughs]

156
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:20,000
This is not a game.

157
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:23,545
Both of us are risking our lives
to change the world, aren't we?

158
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:28,508
I know that, but...
I love you more than the world, Light.

159
00:08:29,009 --> 00:08:30,552
It sounds like you're confused.

160
00:08:30,802 --> 00:08:34,431
Maybe it feels that way to you,
but you're here because you admire Kira.

161
00:08:34,848 --> 00:08:37,559
You don't even know me.
We just met.

162
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,145
Don't you believe in love at first sight?

163
00:08:40,353 --> 00:08:41,229
[Light] No.

164
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:43,565
I admit that everything you said was true.

165
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:47,360
I did want to meet Kira out of gratitude
and respect, not love.

166
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:50,238
But from the moment I first saw you,
I knew.

167
00:08:50,405 --> 00:08:52,449
[Light] What is wrong with this girl?

168
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:54,993
Popular as always.

169
00:08:55,493 --> 00:08:58,496
Well, you can show me your love
by obeying me.

170
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:01,374
I thought you said it was okay
if I used you.

171
00:09:01,624 --> 00:09:04,085
A minute ago, you swore
you'd do anything I asked.

172
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:07,338
Yeah, I did. But I never said
you could date other girls!

173
00:09:07,464 --> 00:09:09,841
I mean, those are two totally
different things.

174
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:13,636
I think you're forgetting
I have both notebooks.

175
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:16,765
If you don't obey me,
I can easily kill you.

176
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:19,893
[Rem] I would never allow that,
Light Yagami.

177
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:24,773
If you do anything
that results in this girl's death,

178
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:27,984
the first thing I'll do is write your name
in my Death Note.

179
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:29,778
I will kill you.

180
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:34,365
I'm sure you realize
that I can see her lifespan.

181
00:09:35,325 --> 00:09:40,371
If she happens to die before that time,
I'll know it was you who killed her.

182
00:09:40,622 --> 00:09:43,208
[Light] But if you were to use
your Death Note to save her,

183
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,001
wouldn't that mean you die, too?

184
00:09:45,752 --> 00:09:48,630
That's right. If you try to save me,
you would die too.

185
00:09:49,089 --> 00:09:50,465
Yes, you are correct.

186
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:53,593
But I'm quite willing
to accept that outcome.

187
00:09:55,345 --> 00:09:57,055
[Light] Is this Shinigami serious?

188
00:09:57,263 --> 00:09:58,223
This is crazy.

189
00:09:58,431 --> 00:10:00,350
-And this means, from now on--
-[knocking on door]

190
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,310
-[Sachiko] Light?
-[gasps]

191
00:10:02,852 --> 00:10:04,395
Yeah, what is it?

192
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:07,524
It's almost 11:30, you know.

193
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:10,110
You really shouldn't have a girl here
this late.

194
00:10:10,527 --> 00:10:11,778
Oh, of course.

195
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:13,571
I guess we lost track of time.

196
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,907
Sorry, Mrs. Yagami.

197
00:10:18,243 --> 00:10:21,121
[Misa] I'm really sorry
for coming over so late at night.

198
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:23,832
-See you later, Light .
-Yeah.

199
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:26,835
Light, you should walk her to the station.

200
00:10:27,127 --> 00:10:28,044
[Light] Eh...

201
00:10:28,545 --> 00:10:31,131
[Light] I can't risk being seen with her
in public.

202
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:35,009
Oh. No, I'm all right, thanks.
Well, good night.

203
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:40,223
Isn't she cute.

204
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:43,351
Yeah, I know. When she got here,
I wasn't so sure,

205
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:45,145
but you're right, she's cute, Mom.

206
00:10:45,395 --> 00:10:46,354
I like her!

207
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:49,732
[Light] That Shinigami is going to kill me
if I kill that girl?

208
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:53,361
Which means... I'm going to have her
hanging around me until she dies?

209
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:55,113
Not only that.

210
00:10:55,238 --> 00:10:56,990
It also means
that I'll be forced to protect her

211
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:59,659
from being caught by the police
for the rest of her life.

212
00:11:02,829 --> 00:11:06,875
Thanks to you, Rem, Light really is
going to be my knight in shining armor.

213
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,126
I suppose.

214
00:11:10,712 --> 00:11:13,381
[Misa] But you can't really kill him,
okay?

215
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:35,778
For a Shinigami to die,

216
00:11:35,862 --> 00:11:38,740
they have to use their Death Note
to save the life of a human.

217
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:41,117
A human whom they have
fallen in love with.

218
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:43,953
Ideally, I could kill Rem first.

219
00:11:44,412 --> 00:11:46,831
Someone I was controlling
would attack Misa,

220
00:11:46,915 --> 00:11:48,625
forcing Rem to save her, but...

221
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,335
No, that would never work.

222
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:53,713
If Misa's life was put in danger,
Rem would immediately suspect me,

223
00:11:53,838 --> 00:11:55,298
and I'd be the one who'd get killed.

224
00:11:56,216 --> 00:12:00,011
[sighs] As things stand,
she's a bigger nuisance than L is.

225
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:03,097
[gasps] She's-- She's famous?

226
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:05,475
Oh. I don't even want to imagine

227
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:07,894
what would happen
if someone found out about us.

228
00:12:09,646 --> 00:12:13,566
Damn it! She's nothing but trouble.
What should I do?

229
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:17,987
No. More importantly, I need to think
of how I can use Misa's eyes

230
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:19,489
to help me kill L.

231
00:12:20,365 --> 00:12:22,325
If I can eliminate him...

232
00:12:25,036 --> 00:12:26,412
[Sayu] Good morning, Light!

233
00:12:27,205 --> 00:12:28,289
Good morning.

234
00:12:28,456 --> 00:12:31,125
Mom, Sayu,
could you do me a big favor

235
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:33,378
and keep Misa a secret
from Dad for now?

236
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:35,088
All right.

237
00:12:35,213 --> 00:12:37,674
Actually, it's not just Dad.

238
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:39,801
You can't tell anyone else
about her either.

239
00:12:40,176 --> 00:12:44,180
You see, Misa's an up-and-coming model
so people can't know about us.

240
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:46,224
What? Is she really?

241
00:12:46,391 --> 00:12:48,268
I thought she was pretty
but I had no idea.

242
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:51,145
That's pretty impressive,
even for you, Light.

243
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:53,898
I'll keep it a secret... for 50 bucks!

244
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:56,943
-[Sachiko] Oh, stop it.
-[Ryuk chuckles]

245
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,987
TO-OH UNIVERSITY

246
00:12:59,362 --> 00:13:01,906
Uh, on page 246...

247
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:04,450
[Light]
Misa's final message should arrive today.

248
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:06,911
Although, before it ever gets
to the TV station,

249
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:09,789
it'll be rerouted
to Task Force headquarters.

250
00:13:09,956 --> 00:13:13,835
I have to go down there at some point
so I can see L's reaction first-hand.

251
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:15,253
[girl] Light. Light?

252
00:13:16,421 --> 00:13:18,047
I thought you and I were
seeing each other.

253
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:20,008
That is, we're more than
just friends, aren't we?

254
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:21,634
Yeah, we are.

255
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:24,637
Exactly. And that's the reason why
I'm sitting next to you in class,

256
00:13:24,804 --> 00:13:26,389
-wouldn't you agree?
-Sure.

257
00:13:26,848 --> 00:13:29,267
But you don't look like
you enjoy being with me.

258
00:13:29,517 --> 00:13:31,728
I mean,
you haven't even looked at me once.

259
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:33,563
That's not true at all.

260
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:35,398
I guess I was just thinking about

261
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:37,650
how everyone's going to be talking
about us now.

262
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:41,571
To think that I'm actually going out with
Miss Takada, the famous Miss Todai.

263
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:44,699
I mean, you're the most beautiful woman
at the school.

264
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:45,742
[Ryuk chuckles]

265
00:13:46,034 --> 00:13:49,078
[clears throat] Why do you even care
about stuff like that?

266
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:53,124
Besides, I hate being called Miss Todai,
or whatever. It's embarrassing.

267
00:13:53,291 --> 00:13:54,792
Yeah, you're right.

268
00:13:55,084 --> 00:13:58,212
[Light] What do you know,
she actually likes all the attention.

269
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:02,008
We should forget about all that stuff
and just go at our own pace.

270
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:03,885
[Takada] Yeah.

271
00:14:08,014 --> 00:14:08,931
[Light] Hello.

272
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:12,477
Oh, come in. Your timing
couldn't be better, actually.

273
00:14:13,186 --> 00:14:16,314
We just received a new video message
from the second Kira.

274
00:14:17,065 --> 00:14:19,400
Huh? Wow, that didn't take long.

275
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:22,195
[L] Yes.
I believe it's the last one.

276
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:24,781
Well, take a look at this.

277
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:28,618
[Second Kira]
I've decided to stop searching for Kira.

278
00:14:28,743 --> 00:14:31,704
And I'd like to thank
the police department for their advice.

279
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:34,791
However, I still plan to help Kira
in his mission.

280
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:38,628
And I hope that in time,
he will come to see me as an ally.

281
00:14:39,253 --> 00:14:42,590
I will start by punishing criminals
that Kira has yet to judge.

282
00:14:43,049 --> 00:14:46,344
Also, I will share my power with others
who I feel are worthy,

283
00:14:46,594 --> 00:14:48,638
and I will encourage them
to do the same.

284
00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:51,307
Together, we'll make this world
a better place.

285
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:54,060
[L] After watching this...

286
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:57,021
I can only think that Kira and
the Second Kira

287
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:58,648
have managed to make contact.

288
00:14:59,816 --> 00:15:01,150
What makes you say that?

289
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:03,152
Oh, come on. Didn't you sense it?

290
00:15:03,361 --> 00:15:05,488
I was sure you'd come to
the same conclusion I did

291
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:07,240
after watching this one through.

292
00:15:07,824 --> 00:15:08,825
[inhales]

293
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,159
Hmm.

294
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:13,579
First, consider how determined he was
to meet Kira.

295
00:15:13,788 --> 00:15:15,331
So why the sudden change of heart?

296
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:18,251
And now he wants to punish criminals
that Kira hasn't?

297
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:22,046
All he wants out of it is for Kira
to see him as an ally? [swallows]

298
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:26,592
It begs the question,
why didn't he do this to begin with?

299
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:29,470
I'm guessing it's because he never thought
that far ahead.

300
00:15:29,554 --> 00:15:33,266
He probably met Kira and was told
which criminals he'd be allowed to judge.

301
00:15:34,684 --> 00:15:38,980
I suspect the purpose of this message
is to hide the fact that they met.

302
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:40,022
[Light] I see.

303
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:43,860
What I find really strange is
that it's unlike Kira to be so careless.

304
00:15:44,235 --> 00:15:45,236
That's true.

305
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:49,699
Hmm. But are we to believe
that Kira made a mistake this time?

306
00:15:49,949 --> 00:15:52,618
Or is this his way of letting us know
that they made contact?

307
00:15:52,702 --> 00:15:55,204
It would be an effective means
of provoking us.

308
00:15:55,413 --> 00:15:57,582
The idea of their union
is very threatening.

309
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:02,003
However, this is also one less reason
to suspect that Light is Kira.

310
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:04,380
[gasps] Ryuzaki,
what do you mean by that?

311
00:16:05,381 --> 00:16:06,966
If Light is Kira,

312
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:10,511
I don't think this is the message
he would have had the Second Kira send us.

313
00:16:10,595 --> 00:16:11,679
It doesn't fit.

314
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:14,557
He would have made the Second Kira
go through with his plan

315
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:15,850
to have me appear on TV.

316
00:16:16,726 --> 00:16:18,394
Then, deny that they ever made contact,

317
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:21,063
letting the Second Kira shoulder the blame
for my death.

318
00:16:21,355 --> 00:16:24,942
He'd make him say something like, hmm...

319
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:28,905
"Although I agreed not to go through
with this,

320
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:32,700
I have come to realize that it was
not Kira's true intention that I stop.

321
00:16:32,909 --> 00:16:35,953
I'm positive that the real Kira
would want L to die.

322
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:38,247
There's no way he'd make me stop."

323
00:16:40,208 --> 00:16:41,667
-[Light] Ryuzaki.
-Yes, Light?

324
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:45,671
I think you're mistaken.
I would never do that if I were Kira.

325
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:46,756
Why not?

326
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:49,008
Well, if you're L and I'm Kira,

327
00:16:49,091 --> 00:16:51,344
then I'd already know your personality
pretty well.

328
00:16:52,053 --> 00:16:56,057
L would never agree to appear on TV,
no matter what threat he was facing.

329
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:58,643
And he wouldn't allow someone else to die
in his place.

330
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:02,563
The L I know would find some way
to escape the situation.

331
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:04,982
So, you figured it out.

332
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:07,276
Look, Light, you've got to stop that.

333
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:09,695
I don't like hearing you say,
"If I were Kira."

334
00:17:09,779 --> 00:17:10,780
Even hypothetically.

335
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:13,032
Oh, I'm sorry, Dad.

336
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:17,495
I just wanted to let Ryuzaki know
exactly what I thought of his plan.

337
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:21,499
I posed that scenario because
I want to help solve this case.

338
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:23,584
It's the only chance I have
to clear my name.

339
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:25,795
Besides, the only reason
I feel comfortable

340
00:17:25,962 --> 00:17:28,881
saying things like that
is because I'm not really Kira.

341
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:31,175
[L] That's a good point.

342
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:33,302
You're not Kira.

343
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:36,973
That is, it would be a problem
if you were Kira.

344
00:17:38,266 --> 00:17:39,225
Because... [sighs]

345
00:17:40,351 --> 00:17:42,937
I feel you're the first friend
that I have ever had.

346
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:44,814
[Ryuk gasps]

347
00:17:48,818 --> 00:17:50,111
[Light] Uh...

348
00:17:50,403 --> 00:17:54,198
Yeah, I know what you mean.
The two of us have a lot in common.

349
00:17:57,368 --> 00:17:58,411
Thank you.

350
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:02,873
And I have missed having you around
at school.

351
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:05,209
We should play tennis again, soon.

352
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,671
Yes, we should.

353
00:18:16,429 --> 00:18:19,223
A friend?
He's your friend?

354
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:21,892
That's a good thing, isn't it, Light?

355
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:25,605
That damn Ryuzaki,
he had no problem figuring out Kira

356
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:28,149
and the Second Kira had made contact
with each other.

357
00:18:28,316 --> 00:18:31,694
-I've got to eliminate him right away.
-I see.

358
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:35,448
[Light] The way things are progressing,
I can't afford to be seen with Misa.

359
00:18:35,573 --> 00:18:37,241
[Misa yells] Light!

360
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:39,535
-[Light grunts]
-I'm sorry,

361
00:18:39,619 --> 00:18:41,537
but I just couldn't wait for two weeks
like you said.

362
00:18:41,704 --> 00:18:45,374
Actually, I was just on my way to
your house when I spotted you. [giggles]

363
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:46,959
[groans]

364
00:18:47,168 --> 00:18:51,297
[Light] This is the first time in my life
that I've been provoked to hit a woman.

365
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:54,175
I... I just wanted to see you so badly.

366
00:18:55,384 --> 00:18:58,054
Well, you might as well come over.

367
00:18:58,137 --> 00:18:59,013
Yay!

368
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:04,477
Another girlfriend?

369
00:19:06,312 --> 00:19:10,858
Oh, great to see you Misa.
I saw you in a whole bunch of magazines.

370
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,569
-Please, come on in.
-[Misa giggles]

371
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:15,112
Sorry to drop by like this.

372
00:19:15,613 --> 00:19:17,239
Could you make us some tea, Mom?

373
00:19:20,701 --> 00:19:21,786
-[Light] Rem.
-Huh?

374
00:19:22,453 --> 00:19:25,164
You are Misa's ally, aren't you?

375
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:30,252
Yes, I'd seen her many times
from the Shinigami realm, and then...

376
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:34,090
certain events made me develop feelings
for her.

377
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:37,051
Feelings? But you're a Shinigami?
[laughs]

378
00:19:37,426 --> 00:19:39,428
You don't like what I said before,

379
00:19:39,512 --> 00:19:43,182
about how I'd kill you
if you even attempted to kill Misa.

380
00:19:43,683 --> 00:19:47,645
So if Misa is happy, does that mean
that you'll be happy as well?

381
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:49,438
I suppose you could say that.

382
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:52,400
I definitely don't want her to suffer.

383
00:19:52,942 --> 00:19:54,276
[Light] As you know...

384
00:19:56,362 --> 00:19:57,738
Misa loves me.

385
00:19:58,280 --> 00:19:59,407
Oh, Light.

386
00:19:59,699 --> 00:20:01,200
-Misa.
-Yes?

387
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:04,787
If I was happy,
would that make you happy, too?

388
00:20:05,162 --> 00:20:07,289
-[Misa] Yes.
-[chuckles]

389
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:10,835
Then, could you ask Rem to kill L?

390
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:12,712
-Huh?
-Rem said

391
00:20:12,795 --> 00:20:14,547
that your happiness was important.

392
00:20:14,672 --> 00:20:17,466
But what do you think would happen
if L caught one of us?

393
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:19,802
It means our happiness would be ruined.

394
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:23,180
[laughs] It's true
that Shinigami are forbidden

395
00:20:23,347 --> 00:20:25,808
to give out a person's name
to anyone.

396
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:29,562
But then again, there's no rule
that prevents Rem from killing anyone.

397
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:31,897
That's right.
And if you agree to kill L,

398
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:34,775
it would only make me love Misa
that much more.

399
00:20:34,984 --> 00:20:36,485
Plus, I'd be grateful to you.

400
00:20:36,569 --> 00:20:39,655
Most importantly, the two of us
would be happy together.

401
00:20:40,281 --> 00:20:43,159
Rem.
I want Light to love me.

402
00:20:43,451 --> 00:20:45,494
And I know we could be happy together.

403
00:20:46,287 --> 00:20:47,830
It's all I ever wanted.

404
00:20:57,214 --> 00:20:58,382
That's a shame.

405
00:21:00,301 --> 00:21:01,385
[Rem] Fine.

406
00:21:02,553 --> 00:21:06,807
As you wish, Light Yagami.
But I do not like you.

407
00:21:07,016 --> 00:21:10,978
This will not kill me, even if it ends up
lengthening your life.

408
00:21:11,604 --> 00:21:13,147
I will kill L for you.

409
00:21:13,898 --> 00:21:17,401
It really makes no difference.
He is just another human to me.

410
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:19,445
Hurray!

411
00:21:19,612 --> 00:21:22,490
Oh, Rem, thank you so much.
I knew I could count on you.

412
00:21:22,615 --> 00:21:23,491
Huh...

413
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:26,327
L will die.

414
00:21:27,161 --> 00:21:28,954
That's all it took?

415
00:21:29,497 --> 00:21:35,294
TO BE CONTINUED

416
00:21:41,967 --> 00:21:46,764
[theme music plays]
